<br>
I hate casinos, personally.  I don't really care for gambling RL, but at least real casinos give you something for your money - the excitement of playing blackjack with other people, the lights and movement of the slot machines, and of course the cheap food and amazing shows (last time I was in Vegas, I didn't spend a dime at the tables, but I saw an incredible Cirque de Soleil production, and had a great time watching all the free promotional things outside the casinos).<br>
<br>
But in EQ, all you do is /random 1000, and when you lose, the casino bot says &quot;So sorry #playername, play again?&quot;  The odds are abysmal, the pitches are annoying, and worst of all, people fall for it.  There's nothing that can get the morons drooling like the thought of something for nothing, of wealth without work.  Everyone hears about the level 53 warrior who won 30 or 50 or 60k, but they never notice the constant stream of sorry-ass level 20s who slink up, drop their 100pp, then lose and slink away again.<br>
<br>
Casinos are stupid.  People who play them and actually think they'll make money are stupid.  And guilds who endorse casinos are downright fucking moronic.<br>
